<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<checkstyle-metadata>
   <module>
      <check fully-qualified-name="com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.checks.UpperEllCheck"
             name="UpperEll"
             parent="com.puppycrawl.tools.checkstyle.TreeWalker">
         <description>&lt;div&gt;
 Checks that long constants are defined with an upper ell. That is &lt;code&gt;'L'&lt;/code&gt;
 and not &lt;code&gt;'l'&lt;/code&gt;. This is in accordance with the Java Language Specification,
 &lt;a href="https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se11/html/jls-3.html#jls-3.10.1"&gt;
 Section 3.10.1&lt;/a&gt;.
 &lt;/div&gt;

 &lt;p&gt;
 Rationale: The lower-case ell &lt;code&gt;'l'&lt;/code&gt; looks a lot like &lt;code&gt;1&lt;/code&gt;.
 &lt;/p&gt;</description>
         <message-keys>
            <message-key key="upperEll"/>
         </message-keys>
      </check>
   </module>
</checkstyle-metadata>
